              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "To locate resoances and for exitation function:",
                "A set of three targets was made by collecting 100 eV",
                "24Mg+,25Mg+ and 26Mg+ions in amounts of 2.5 micro-g/cm2",
                "on 0.4 mm thick tantalum backings.",
                "For resonance stregth measurements:",
                "The tagets were prepared by evaporating pure (99.9%)",
                "natural Mg onto 0.4 mm thick tantalum backings in a",
                "vacuum of 100 micro-Pa. The target thikness was",
                "30 micro-g/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " An 110 cm**3 Ge(Li) with an energy resolution",
                "1.9 keV at 1.33 MeV and 2.9 keV at 2.61 MeV and an",
                "efficiency of 21.8% was used to detect the gamma-rays.",
                "The detector was placed at a distance of 5 cm from the",
                "target.The absolute efficiency of the detector was",
                "determined in with the calibrated IAEA standard sources",
                "and using gamma-rays  from reaction 27Al(p,gamma)28Si",
                "at Ep=992 keV.",
                "For angular distribution correction gamma-ray yield was",
                "measured at angles 0, 30, 45, 60 and 90 degrees. The",
                "yields were monitored by 66 cm3 Ge(Li) detector placed",
                "at a fixed position at a distance of 10 cm from target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "In REACTIONs FCT=1/(2Jp+1)(2Jt+1),",
                "where is Jp = spin of incident projectile and",
                "Jt = spin of target nucleus.",
                "In the formula of resonance strength:",
                "          g*Gamma(i)Gamma(j)/Gamma(tot)",
                "instead of usual statistical weight:",
                "  g=(2J+1)/(2Jp+1)(2Jt+1), the authors used g=(2J+1)"
              ]
            }
          ],
